1️⃣ Sidekiq Web UI (Recommended)

Start Sidekiq with the Web UI mounted in Rails:

# config/routes.rb
require 'sidekiq/web'
mount Sidekiq::Web => '/sidekiq'


Then visit: http://yourapp.com/sidekiq

You can see:

Busy → jobs currently executing

Queues → jobs waiting in each queue

Scheduled → jobs set to run in the future

Retry → jobs that failed and will retry

Dead → jobs that failed permanently

2️⃣ Sidekiq CLI commands

Sidekiq comes with a sidekiq CLI, but for inspecting jobs, you usually use sidekiqctl:

# Check process stats
sidekiqctl stats /path/to/sidekiq.pid


This gives you: processed, failed, busy, scheduled, retries, etc.

For more detailed info, you can use redis-cli because Sidekiq stores queues in Redis:

# List all queues
redis-cli LLEN queue:default  # pending jobs in 'default' queue

# List scheduled jobs
redis-cli ZRANGE schedule 0 -1

3️⃣ Programmatically in Rails console

You can inspect Sidekiq queues directly from Rails:

# All queue names
Sidekiq::Queue.all.map(&:name)  

# Jobs in a specific queue
queue = Sidekiq::Queue.new("default")
queue.size          # number of jobs
queue.each do |job|
  puts job.klass    # class name
  puts job.args     # arguments
  puts job.jid      # job ID
end

# Scheduled jobs
schedule = Sidekiq::ScheduledSet.new
schedule.each do |job|
  puts "#{job.klass} will run at #{Time.at(job.at)}"
end

# Retry jobs
retry_set = Sidekiq::RetrySet.new
retry_set.each do |job|
  puts "#{job.klass} will retry at #{Time.at(job.at)}"
end

# Dead jobs
dead_set = Sidekiq::DeadSet.new
dead_set.each do |job|
  puts "#{job.klass} failed permanently at #{Time.at(job.failed_at)}"
end

4️⃣ Summary Table

| Job type          | How to check                                |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| Queued            | `Sidekiq::Queue` or Web UI queues           |
| Scheduled         | `Sidekiq::ScheduledSet` or Web UI scheduled |
| Retry             | `Sidekiq::RetrySet` or Web UI retry tab     |
| Dead / Failed     | `Sidekiq::DeadSet` or Web UI dead tab       |
| Currently running | Web UI busy tab, or `Sidekiq::Workers`      |
